                            <h3 class="text-brand">#Zostanwdomu Poland</h3>

                            <p>Google has launch the COVID19 mobility reports. I think there is very valuable
                                information on these reports to identify if on reality people are staying at home or
                                not. The baseline is the median value, for the corresponding day of the week, during the
                                5- week period Jan 3–Feb 6, 2020. What can we learn for Poland? Mobility to retail and
                                recreation has reduce in 78%, this compared to Spain that has reduce to 94%, there is
                                still area to improve the #stayingathome for these areas. To parks people has just drop
                                to 59%, in Spain this drop has been to 89%. These is most difficult in my opinion
                                because the weather has improve in Poland but if we can reduce the risk of contagious we
                                need to reduce the amount of people going to parks. Regarding workplaces, in Poland the
                                reduction has been 36% compared to Spain that is 64% and this makes perfect sense since
                                we have not been in a total lockdown.
                            </p>
                            <img class="post-img img-responsive text-center" src="assets/images/polandgoogle1.jpg"
                                alt="">
                                 <img class="post-img img-responsive text-center" src="assets/images/polandgoogle2.jpg"
                                alt="">
                            <h4 class="text-brand">Death Rate Poland</h4>
                            <div id="graficaPolonia"></div>
                            <p>This is the death rate of Poland. I have been surprise on the last days that the number
                                of deaths have been more than the trendline. This means that the death rate is
                                increasing compared to the past trend.</p>


                            <h3 class="text-brand">#QuedateEnCasa Mexico</h3>
                            <p>Now let’s see Mexico report. The people reducing the mobility to retail and recreation
                                activities is very low, just a 45% reduction. To parks the reduction has been 46% and to
                                workplaces a 20%. Mexico people are still going out. It is very important to note that
                                unless people stop going out the infection rate will not go down.
                            </p>

                            <img class="post-img img-responsive text-center" src="assets/images/mxgoogle1.jpg" alt="">
                            <img class="post-img img-responsive text-center" src="assets/images/mxgoogle2.jpg" alt="">
